description:
This data driven role offers you the opportunity to make an impact as a key part of the team that manages all of our juicy call center data and customer contact metrics in an effort to provide outstanding customer service to our wireless customers nationwide. You will provide reporting and actionable analysis to support operations and drive constant improvement in our customer experience. You will work with a variety of internal and external groups, enabling you to expand your knowledge and experience, and gain broad exposure to our organization. We are both customer focused and data driven, so your input will be highly valued.
You will report to the Manager of Customer Service and take direction from the Director of Customer Service.
We’re looking for someone who loves numbers, loves business, loves data and loves mixing all three to make a positive impact on our customers’ experience and the bottom line. You will interact with a wide-range of people in a very fast paced environment where constant change is the norm. You will spot trends in our data and provide clear reporting on call center performance.
To be a good fit for the Customer Service Data Analyst opportunity, you should have:
The Role:
The role is diverse and in addition to pulling regular reports, you will handle a variety of ad hoc analyses. A large part of the role will be capturing data in our IVR, CRM and Billing Systems to answer the “Why?” You will spot trends in our data, provide clear reporting on call center performance, establish metrics and review analytics, propose, implement and measure strategies to improve the experience of our customers.
More specifically, you will:
Interpret call center metrics;
Provide reporting on customer satisfaction;
Use data to identify trends and issues that provide opportunities for improvements in customer service;
Provide ad-hoc actionable analysis to the customer service team and others in the company to help them understand our customers; and
Manage data that drives our customer service systems including our CRM, Billing and IVR platforms.
CREDO Mobile, a successful wireless company, exists to help build a just, humane, and environmentally sustainable world. We donate a portion of our revenue to nonprofit groups working for peace, human rights, equality and the environment. We also serve as a strong political force, with over 4 million online activists, dedicated to giving our customers the opportunity to speak out on critical public issues through our Web site and monthly bills.
Interested parties should submit a resume, salary history and a cover letter. In your cover letter, please provide an example of when you worked with messy data and helped make a decision based on that data. Salary based on experience and includes complete benefits package.

Bachelors degree and at least 2-3 years experience;
Outstanding quantitative and analytic skills;
Demonstrated ability to effectively communicate analyses to others;
Comfortable with large amounts of data and proficient with SQL;
Excellent Excel skills;
Call center data analysis or customer service experience;
Experience with Salesforce CRM and IVR reporting considered a plus; and
A strong team player.

Temporary
Position Summary:

The Data Analyst 1 takes primary ownership of the Operations Team’s metrics and quality monitoring using metrics based on both advanced molecular biology and cutting-edge statistical algorithms.

Primary Responsibilities:
Assist with designing and building analytics reporting using business intelligence tools and database;
Support Operations with data and metrics for operational performance monitoring and investigations;
Perform statistical analysis on production data sets to discover trends and develop business insights;
Develop metrics for measuring and understanding laboratory operations efficiency and effectiveness;
Investigate data quality concerns using a variety of tools such as SQL, Excel, or similar;
Coordinate new feature requests that may stem from the investigations;
Interface with other groups within the company, especially statistics and software engineering;
This role works with PHI on a regular basis both in paper and electronic form and have an access to various technologies to access PHI (paper and electronic) in order to perform the job;
Employee must complete training relating to HIPAA/PHI privacy, General Policies and Procedure Compliance training and security training as soon as possible but not later than the first 30 days of hire;
Must maintain a current status on Natera training requirements;
Employee must pass post offer criminal background check.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Management, Statistics, Business Analytics, or equivalent; MSc preferred;
1+ years of overall data centric experience preferred; preferably in business data analysis;
Some laboratory or molecular biology experience is preferred;
Experience with reporting packages (such as QlikView, Tableau, Business Objects etc.) is a plus.
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy;
Technical expertise regarding data models, database query, data segmentation techniques;
Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings;
Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (e.g. Excel);
Excellent organizational, communication, presentation, and facilitation skills.
Strong knowledge of databases (SQL etc.) Basic understanding on ETL frameworks;
SQL programming;
Basic understanding with business intelligence tools;
Microsoft Office / Google Docs and Windows workstation;
Instant message tools (e.g. Slack, Google Hangouts).
Physical Demands and Work Environment:
Duties are typically performed in an office setting.
The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to talk or hear.
This position requires the ability to use a computer keyboard, communicate over the telephone and read printed material.
OUR OPPORTUNITY

Driven by the passion for elevating the science and utility of genetic testing, Natera is committed to helping families identify and manage genetic diseases. Natera is a rapidly-growing diagnostics company with proprietary bioinformatics and molecular technology for analyzing DNA. Our complex technology has been proven clinically and commercially in the prenatal testing space and we are actively researching its applications in the liquid biopsy space for developing products with oncology applications.

The Natera team consists of highly dedicated statisticians, geneticists, doctors, laboratory scientists, business professionals, software engineers and many other professionals from world-class institutions, who care deeply for our work and each other. When you join Natera, you’ll work hard and grow quickly. Working alongside the elite of the industry, you’ll be stretched and challenged, and take pride in being part of a company that is changing the landscape of genetic disease management.

WHAT WE OFFER

Competitive Benefits. Healthy catered lunches, Premium snacks and beverages, Onsite gym with cardio and weight-training equipment, Game room with satellite TV, Onsite dry cleaning and alteration service with pick-up and delivery, Employee-organized sport leagues, Happy hours and BBQs, Generous Employee Referral program.

For more information, visit www.natera.com.

Natera is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer.

JOB PURPOSE
Intercontinental Exchange (NYSE: ICE) is a Fortune 500 company that operates global markets and clearing houses, and delivers information and technology designed to help companies around the world manage risk, access information and raise capital. We serve customers in over 70 countries with a team of world-class employees. We recruit passionate, knowledgeable professionals and offer a collaborative, results-oriented environment where they help build innovative solutions to help our customers thrive in global markets.

At Intercontinental Exchange, our diverse team is working to create and improve technology that solves market structure challenges for market participants around the world. Whether it’s designing and managing the tech infrastructure for global trading and clearing or developing leading-edge market data solutions, our teams are a critical part of global markets.

As we continue to grow and expand, we’re looking for motivated, results-oriented professionals who share our entrepreneurial spirit and commitment to improving the global marketplace. We offer a comprehensive and competitive compensation and benefits package to ensure the health and financial security of our employees.

Our Dublin office is primarily focused on data collection and consists of the different departments such as Equities, Funds, Fixed Income and Masterfile. This role is pivotal to the data collection process. The data we maintain enables us to provide a variety of market trusted products to our clients. All our Analysts are multilingual and are assigned to a geographical territory depending on their spoken languages.

DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
Researching, capturing and inputting market data in a timely and accurate manner for our covered markets;
Identifying data quality issues, recommending procedural and technical changes to improve productivity and data quality for ICE Data Services;
The Research Analyst will be expected to stay current in Industry initiatives and organizations that impact the data covered;
Assist in ICE Data Services Data Quality Program;
Address client inquiries on EMEA Markets;
Confirm existing information and/or provide additional information when internal and external customers inquire about data discrepancies;
Research information on initial sources and may have verbal discussions with underwriters, financial advisors, agencies, trustees, etc.
Work with Data Collection and Product to achieve common goals of improving data quality, accuracy and timeliness;
Communicate, verbal and written, with Customer Services and Evaluated Services;
Maintain daily and monthly statistics and metrics of client inquiries.

This is a research position and not a technical IT role.

Shift Rota: 10:30 to 20:00 depending on business requirement, additional hours maybe required as and when needed and occasional weekend work. The role will be expected to work bank holidays as per the market covered.

PERSON SPECIFICATION

Essential
Strong interpersonal, reading and written communication skills;
Business level English (reading, writing and spoken) and also fluency in another language - like Hungarian, German, French, Dutch, Hebrew, Korean, Japanese, Chinese dialect - Mandarin or Cantonese or Malay would be an advantage.

Desirable
Experience in a similar field or has conducted research extensively as part of a degree or the working environment. Applicants without experience can apply as training will be provided;
Good PC skill would be advantage.

We offer experience working in dynamic, professional, fast paced environment, friendly and multicultural colleagues and robust career progression.

We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of gender, civil status, family status, sexual orientation, religion, age, disability, race or membership of the travelling community.
